      • setAuthorName

        @NotNull
public @NotNull EmbedEditor setAuthorName(@Nullable
                                                    @Nullable String authorName)
        Sets the author of the Embed.
        The author appears in the top left of the Embed with its name being made clickable by way of providing an url.
        This convenience method just sets the name.
        Example
        Parameters:
        authorName - The name of the author of the Embed. If this is not set, the author will not appear in the Embed.
        Returns:
        The editor after the author has been set.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If name is longer than characters, as defined by Embed.AUTHOR_MAX_LENGTH.

      • setAuthor

        @NotNull
public @NotNull EmbedEditor setAuthor(@Nullable
                                                @Nullable String authorName,
                                                @Nullable
                                                @Nullable String authorURL)
        Sets the author of the embed.
        The author appears in the top left of the embed and can have a small image beside it along with the author's name being made clickable by way of providing an url.
        This convenience method sets the name and the url.
        Example
        Parameters:
        authorName - The name of the author of the embed. If this is not set, the author will not appear in the embed.
        authorURL - The url of the author of the embed.
        Returns:
        The editor after the author has been set.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException -
        • If the character limit for name, defined by Embed.AUTHOR_MAX_LENGTH as , is exceeded.
        • If the character limit for url, defined by Embed.URL_MAX_LENGTH as , is exceeded.
        • If the provided url is not a properly formatted http or https url.

      • getEmbedTitle

        @NotNull
public @NotNull String getEmbedTitle()
                                        throws IOException
        The title of the Embed.
        Typically, this will be the html title of the webpage that is being embedded.
        The only difference between this and Embed.getTitle() is that this method gets the current title of the Tixte 'Embed Editor' page, while Embed.getTitle() only gets the current value of the variable.
        Returns:
        Possibly-empty string containing the title of the embedded resource.
        Throws:
        IOException - If the request could not be executed due to cancellation, a connectivity problem or timeout. Because networks can fail during an exchange, it is possible that the remote server accepted the request before the failure.

      • getEmbedDescription

        @NotNull
public @NotNull String getEmbedDescription()
                                              throws IOException
        The description of the embedded resource.
        This is provided only if Discord could find a description for the embedded resource using the provided url.
        Commonly, this is null. Be careful when using it.
        The only difference between this and Embed.getDescription() is that this method gets the current description of the Tixte 'Embed Editor' page, while Embed.getDescription() only gets the current value of the variable.
        Returns:
        Possibly-empty string containing a description of the embedded resource.
        Throws:
        IOException - If the request could not be executed due to cancellation, a connectivity problem or timeout. Because networks can fail during an exchange, it is possible that the remote server accepted the request before the failure.
